# CS 6378 Assignment 3 - C++ Conversion
## Hi, I'm Simran Misra

This project is a C++17 conversion of the original Java client/server distributed key-value store.

## Layout
- `server/` contains the C++ server implementation.
- `client/` contains the C++ client implementation.
- `server-hostnames.txt` is the shared host list used by both programs.

## Build
From `client/` or `server/`, run:

```bash
make
```

## Run
Start a server on each hostname listed in `server-hostnames.txt`:

```bash
cd server
./execute.sh
```

Run client operations:

```bash
cd client
./execute.sh GET <KEY>
./execute.sh PUT <KEY> <VALUE>
```

## Notes
The Java implementation used Java Object Serialization. The C++ implementation uses a simple length-prefixed text protocol, so C++ clients interoperate with C++ servers, not with the original Java binaries.
